<HEADLINE>
<P>
MURAL SHOWING LENIN DEFACED BY FIREBOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AUSTIN, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A homemade firebomb was thrown against a painting of Soviet revolutionary 
leader V.I. Lenin on the outside wall of a bar, firefighters said. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to Lenin, the mural depicts the hammer and sickle and a happy face. 
</P>
<P>
The incendiary device, made from a bottle containing about a quart of a 
flammable liquid, caused slight damage to the Eastern Bloc bar, fire officials 
said. The bar was not open at the time of the incident Sunday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
