SLIDE CLOSES ROAD TO SCENIC PRESERVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CEDAR CITY, Utah 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A massive mudslide blocked the main road to Cedar Breaks National Monument, 
stripped off a section of pavement half a mile long and continued to ooze 
downhill Monday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The slide, roughly half a mile long and half a mile wide, broke loose sometime 
during the night and sent mud and boulders cascading across State Road 14, Kim 
Morris of the state Department of Transportation said. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported, Morris said, and visitors to the monument were able 
to take other roads out. 
