<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: HOUSE OF FABRICS PROFIT RISES 9% FOR 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
House of Fabrics said its fiscal fourth-quarter profit rose 9% from a year 
earlier on a 10% increase in sales. 
</P>
<P>
The Sherman Oaks company, which operates a chain of 653 fabric and 
sewing-accessories stores, said net income in the quarter that ended Jan. 31 
climbed to $4.73 million from $4.33 million, and sales increased to $100.8 
million from $91.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
House of Fabrics attributed the gains to its recent restructuring, in which the 
company phased out many of its smaller mall stores and opened larger, 
stand-alone outlets. The new stores are more popular because they offer more 
merchandise and are more convenient for customers, House of Fabrics contends. 
</P>
<P>
For its full fiscal year, House of Fabrics' profit rose 9% to $11.4 million 
from $10.5 million, and its annual sales were up 5% to $338 million from $322.5 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
