<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: STILL TRYING TO MAKE BOGGS DEAL, RED SOX REPORTEDLY TALK WITH ROYALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Boston Red Sox, stepping up their attempts to trade controversial star Wade 
Boggs, talked to the Kansas City Royals last weekend about a deal for the 
five-time American League batting champion. 
</P>
<P>
Royals General Manager John Schuerholz told the Kansas City Star that talks 
have taken place but would not identify the Royal players involved and said 
chances of a deal are slim. 
</P>
<P>
The Royals executive described Boggs' personal problems as "somewhat 
disconcerting." 
</P>
<P>
The revelations resulting from Boggs' relationship with Margo Adams have 
troubled Red Sox brass, which was further angered by his appearance last week 
with Barbara Walters on "20/20." The team has since stepped up efforts to trade 
Boggs. 
</P>
