<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BREA; 
</P>
<P>
MAN HELD IN KIDNAPING OF TEEN-AGE RELATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brea police on Monday arrested a 28-year-old man on suspicion of kidnaping and 
sexually assaulting a 17-year-old female relative about 3 months ago. 
</P>
<P>
Juan Jaracuaro Orozco of Brea was arrested at his workplace in the city without 
incident, Police Lt. Jim Winder said. 
</P>
<P>
Winder said the arrest concluded a 3-month investigation of the girl's report 
that she had been abducted and molested by a relative. Winder said police are 
not releasing information about how the girl is related to Orozco. 
</P>
<P>
Winder said the girl had been kidnaped from her home in Brea and taken by car 
on a 4-day journey covering a large geographical area. 
</P>
<P>
"She suffered psychological trauma, but she was not physically injured," Winder 
said. He added that the girl is now back in Brea and is recovering 
satisfactorily from the ordeal. 
</P>
<P>
Orozco is being held at the Orange County Jail in lieu of $100,000 bail, Winder 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
