<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE/TECHNOLOGY; 
</P>
<P>
AST RESEARCH SELLS CAMINTONN UNIT TO MANAGEMENT FOR UNDISCLOSED SUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by David Olmos, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AST Research Inc. has sold its Camintonn division, which makes computer 
enhancements for use on Digital Equipment Corp. products, to Camintonn 
management for an undisclosed sum. 
</P>
<P>
AST, an Irvine computer maker, had previously disclosed plans to sell the 
operation as part of a strategy to focus on its principal business: selling 
personal computers and related products compatible with International Business 
Machines systems. 
</P>
<P>
As a result of expenses from the sale, AST recorded a pretax charge to earnings 
of $3 million for the quarter ended Dec. 30. 
</P>
<P>
Camintonn, based in Irvine, manufactures add-on computer boards and laser 
printers for Digital Equipment computers. It employs 21 people. 
</P>
<P>
Bosco K. Sun, formerly general manager of AST's Camintonn division, will serve 
as president and chief executive of the newly independent company. 
</P>
<P>
"We are pleased that Camintonn will continue to serve the DEC marketplace," 
said Bruce Edwards, AST's chief financial officer. "The sale to a group of AST 
employees is important in maintaining the continuity of Camintonn's service to 
its customers." 
</P>
</TEXT>
