<P>
NUCLEAR ACCIDENT MARKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HARRISBURG, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anti-nuclear activists marked the 10th anniversary of the Three Mile Island 
nuclear plant accident, the nation's worst, with renewed warnings Monday that 
the health effects were hidden and the lessons forgotten. About 150 people 
marched in a procession outside the plant for just over an hour late in the 
afternoon. 
</P>
