<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUSSIAN WATCHES TO BE MARKETED IN THE U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WILKES-BARRE, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Russian watches, the ultimate anti-status status symbol, will be available in 
the United States this summer, Gruen Marketing Corp. said. 
</P>
<P>
Gruen said it had secured the rights to market Soviet-made watches, including 
the Russian military-style quartz watch that features CCCP (Union of Soviet 
Socialist Republics) and Soviet on the dial, through Wenger Ltd., a Canadian 
watch company. 
</P>
<P>
Wenger has North American distribution rights through Vremex, the official 
Soviet agency for Russian watches. 
</P>
<P>
Gruen said it has already received commitments from a number of leading 
department stores, including Bloomingdale's and Saks Fifth Avenue and will 
begin marketing the watches June 29. It did not disclose prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
